description: The fund’s investment adviser (the “Adviser”) seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing the fund’s assets in liquid U.S. electricity futures and carbon allowance futures contracts that are contained in the index or have characteristics that the Adviser believes make their return performance likely to be highly correlated to futures contracts that are contained in the index. The index tracks the broad U.S. electricity market on a carbon-neutral basis. The fund is non-diversified.
name: CNIC ICE U.S. Carbon Neutral Power Futures Index ETF
